1
00:00:08,300 --> 00:00:09,700
I need to leave.

2
00:00:09,833 --> 00:00:11,667
I have something important
to take care of.

3
00:00:11,800 --> 00:00:12,767
What is it?

4
00:00:12,900 --> 00:00:16,433
Something I should have done
a long time ago.

5
00:00:16,567 --> 00:00:17,367
I cannot do this anymore!

6
00:00:17,500 --> 00:00:18,400
Paolo, I still want this.

7
00:00:18,533 --> 00:00:19,833
- Please.
- No. We are done.

8
00:00:19,967 --> 00:00:21,167
What we have is great!

9
00:00:21,300 --> 00:00:22,700
This is over!

10
00:00:22,833 --> 00:00:25,000
Paolo, one last time.

11
00:00:25,133 --> 00:00:27,600
One last time together.

12
00:00:27,733 --> 00:00:29,067
Kind Brother!

13
00:00:30,500 --> 00:00:31,400
Jobert?

14
00:01:16,367 --> 00:01:18,567
Ma'am, please.

15
00:01:18,700 --> 00:01:20,567
Please speak with Sir Greg.

16
00:01:20,700 --> 00:01:22,500
Please convince him
not to dismiss me.

17
00:01:22,633 --> 00:01:23,600
Please make him change his mind!

18
00:01:23,733 --> 00:01:25,733
He might still change his mind,
Ma'am.

19
00:01:25,867 --> 00:01:29,133
Yolly, if that is Greg's
decision, that is final.

20
00:01:29,267 --> 00:01:32,400
I do not want us to argue
about this as well.

21
00:01:32,533 --> 00:01:35,133
My marriage is already
hanging on by a thread.

22
00:01:35,267 --> 00:01:36,600
That is what I need to save.

23
00:01:36,733 --> 00:01:38,367
Not you.

24
00:01:38,500 --> 00:01:41,633
Ma'am, is that all there is
to it?

25
00:01:41,800 --> 00:01:45,600
Ma'am, I have served you
for many years.

26
00:01:45,733 --> 00:01:48,600
I endured all the
difficult moments.

27
00:01:48,733 --> 00:01:51,267
Not even once, Ma'am,
did you hear me complain.

28
00:01:51,400 --> 00:01:52,800
I never complained.

29
00:01:52,933 --> 00:01:54,567
This is the only time
I am asking you.

30
00:01:54,700 --> 00:01:57,233
This is my last request, Ma'am!

31
00:01:57,367 --> 00:02:01,300
You refused me and dismissed me
so easily!

32
00:02:01,433 --> 00:02:03,400
Ma'am, please!

33
00:02:03,533 --> 00:02:05,000
Yolly.

34
00:02:05,133 --> 00:02:06,000
[Shushes]

35
00:02:06,133 --> 00:02:08,300
[Sobbing]

36
00:02:08,433 --> 00:02:10,300
Yolly.

37
00:02:10,433 --> 00:02:13,300
Yolly.

38
00:02:13,433 --> 00:02:17,233
You may stay in the mansion
for one month.

39
00:02:17,400 --> 00:02:21,100
That is your reward for
your years of service.

40
00:02:21,233 --> 00:02:27,167
This will help you find a place
and repay your advances.

41
00:02:27,300 --> 00:02:28,400
I do not want that, Ma'am!

42
00:02:28,533 --> 00:02:29,900
Please!

43
00:02:30,033 --> 00:02:32,233
Please do not send me away.

44
00:02:32,367 --> 00:02:33,267
Yolly...

45
00:02:33,400 --> 00:02:34,933
Please, Ma'am!

46
00:02:35,067 --> 00:02:36,700
Yolly. Yolly!

47
00:02:38,100 --> 00:02:44,933
- Yolly!
- I do not want to leave!

48
00:02:45,067 --> 00:02:47,267
Yoully, Yolly.

49
00:02:47,400 --> 00:02:48,567
[Sobbing]

50
00:02:48,733 --> 00:02:50,400
PLease...

51
00:02:50,533 --> 00:02:53,433
Stop polluting my room
with your negative aura.

52
00:02:55,100 --> 00:02:57,100
Please get me some jasmine tea.

53
00:02:57,233 --> 00:02:59,067
Yolly, please.

54
00:03:24,900 --> 00:03:25,733
Jobert?

55
00:03:25,867 --> 00:03:27,233
Where is Mama?

56
00:03:27,367 --> 00:03:29,433
- Please bring Mama back.
- Jobert!

57
00:03:29,567 --> 00:03:30,333
Mama!

58
00:03:30,467 --> 00:03:34,633
- Mama!
- Jobert!

59
00:03:34,767 --> 00:03:35,800
I'm here, it's okay.

60
00:03:35,933 --> 00:03:38,467
Ma'am Marj, Jobert is looking
for your mother.

61
00:03:38,600 --> 00:03:40,233
- Mama!
- I said I don't know

62
00:03:40,367 --> 00:03:41,300
where she is.

63
00:03:41,433 --> 00:03:43,900
Jobert, I'm looking for Mama,
okay?

64
00:03:44,033 --> 00:03:46,100
I'm looking for mother, okay?

65
00:03:46,233 --> 00:03:47,333
Please bring Mama back.

66
00:03:47,467 --> 00:03:49,967
I want to see Mama.

67
00:03:50,100 --> 00:03:51,367
Look for Mama.

68
00:03:51,500 --> 00:03:52,833
Jobert, I'm here.

69
00:03:53,900 --> 00:03:55,200
- Mama!
- Jobert!

70
00:03:55,333 --> 00:03:56,233
Where's Mama?

71
00:03:56,367 --> 00:03:57,967
Can you get his earphones,
please.

72
00:03:59,033 --> 00:04:02,167
Jobert, I'm here. Calm down,
okay?

73
00:04:02,300 --> 00:04:04,767
- I'm looking for Mama.
- Ma'am Marj, here.

74
00:04:04,900 --> 00:04:07,400
Where's Mama?

75
00:04:07,533 --> 00:04:08,333
Here, here, here.

76
00:04:08,467 --> 00:04:10,400
Calm down, I'm here.

77
00:04:10,533 --> 00:04:11,767
I won't leave you.

78
00:04:11,900 --> 00:04:14,633
I want to see Mama.

79
00:04:14,767 --> 00:04:16,433
- Bring her back.
- Yes.

80
00:04:16,567 --> 00:04:18,133
She's gone.

81
00:04:18,267 --> 00:04:20,267
[PHONE RINGING]

82
00:04:20,400 --> 00:04:21,400
Wait a minute.

83
00:04:24,200 --> 00:04:25,667
Hello, Dr. Alvarez.

84
00:04:25,800 --> 00:04:27,600
I am sorry I missed your call.

85
00:04:27,767 --> 00:04:29,633
My sibling had
a medical episode.

86
00:04:29,767 --> 00:04:31,600
<i>I just call you to let you know</i>

87
00:04:31,733 --> 00:04:34,467
<i>that Jasmine's test results are
back.</i>

88
00:04:34,600 --> 00:04:37,100
<i>And we can see that her body can
handle it.</i>

89
00:04:37,233 --> 00:04:40,633
<i>We can begin induction
chemotherapy treatment.</i>

90
00:04:40,767 --> 00:04:41,500
What?

91
00:04:43,467 --> 00:04:45,200
My child needs chemotherapy?

92
00:04:52,967 --> 00:04:53,833
Ash...

93
00:04:56,433 --> 00:04:58,167
I am scared.

94
00:04:58,300 --> 00:05:01,100
Like, for real.

95
00:05:01,267 --> 00:05:02,067
Jas...

96
00:05:02,200 --> 00:05:03,833
What are you thinking?

97
00:05:03,967 --> 00:05:05,400
You got this.

98
00:05:05,533 --> 00:05:07,867
But, what if, I'll look like
what I've watched.

99
00:05:08,933 --> 00:05:11,300
Like hair loss.

100
00:05:11,433 --> 00:05:12,533
Like super thin.

101
00:05:14,533 --> 00:05:16,233
They looked like zombies.

102
00:05:16,367 --> 00:05:17,833
Don't say that.

103
00:05:17,967 --> 00:05:20,333
They're not zombies, okay?

104
00:05:20,467 --> 00:05:23,033
They are fighters.

105
00:05:23,167 --> 00:05:25,167
Just like you.

106
00:05:25,300 --> 00:05:26,333
Because I'm just worried

107
00:05:26,467 --> 00:05:29,733
that my therapy will fail again.

108
00:05:29,867 --> 00:05:31,933
Just like what happened
in Hong Kong.

109
00:05:32,067 --> 00:05:34,900
This time is different, Jas.

110
00:05:35,067 --> 00:05:37,333
You are stronger now.

111
00:05:37,467 --> 00:05:38,500
Right?

112
00:05:38,633 --> 00:05:40,500
Thank you, Ash.

113
00:05:40,633 --> 00:05:44,500
You are the only one
who calms me.

114
00:05:44,633 --> 00:05:49,733
I'm here for you.

115
00:05:49,867 --> 00:05:50,567
Oh, your phone.

116
00:05:50,700 --> 00:06:00,667
[PHONE VIBRATING]

117
00:06:01,067 --> 00:06:02,033
Xander?

118
00:06:04,500 --> 00:06:05,233
Yeah.

119
00:06:06,500 --> 00:06:07,867
I'm going to miss him, Ash.

120
00:06:10,100 --> 00:06:11,633
Ash...

121
00:06:11,767 --> 00:06:14,100
I'll leave him to you, okay?

122
00:06:14,233 --> 00:06:16,700
Just hang out with him,
so he doesn't feel lonely.

123
00:06:16,833 --> 00:06:17,733
While I'm not around.

124
00:06:19,367 --> 00:06:20,700
I promise, Jas.

125
00:06:29,367 --> 00:06:30,400
It's okay.

126
00:06:31,867 --> 00:06:33,633
Everything will be all right.

127
00:06:41,967 --> 00:06:46,067
Marj!

128
00:06:46,200 --> 00:06:47,467
I went to the precinct

129
00:06:47,600 --> 00:06:49,833
and to all of the hospitals.

130
00:06:49,967 --> 00:06:51,433
But I didn't see her there.

131
00:06:56,000 --> 00:06:57,800
Everything's going to be okay.

132
00:06:59,067 --> 00:07:03,133
I don't know what to do with
everything that is happening.

133
00:07:05,967 --> 00:07:07,000
Mama is missing.

134
00:07:07,133 --> 00:07:08,500
I do not know where to find her.

135
00:07:08,633 --> 00:07:11,767
And then the doctor called,

136
00:07:11,900 --> 00:07:15,500
Jasmine needs to undergo
with chemotherapy.

137
00:07:15,667 --> 00:07:16,567
What?

138
00:07:17,200 --> 00:07:19,500
I do not know what to deal with
first.

139
00:07:22,833 --> 00:07:24,533
I am trying to endure it,

140
00:07:24,667 --> 00:07:27,267
but I am breaking down.

141
00:07:27,400 --> 00:07:32,900
[SOBBING]

142
00:07:33,033 --> 00:07:35,467
I'm also neglecting you, too.

143
00:07:36,233 --> 00:07:39,900
I have so much shortcomings.

144
00:07:40,033 --> 00:07:42,567
I know that I haven't been
a good wife to you.

145
00:07:46,733 --> 00:07:48,900
It's okay.

146
00:07:49,067 --> 00:07:50,900
Remember?

147
00:07:51,033 --> 00:07:53,900
I'm always here for you.

148
00:07:54,033 --> 00:07:56,600
I'm here for Jasmine too.

149
00:07:56,733 --> 00:08:00,233
I will ask the maids to help out
for Jobert, okay?

150
00:08:00,367 --> 00:08:04,133
And, I'll have the people
to help us out

151
00:08:04,267 --> 00:08:05,933
looking for your mother.

152
00:08:07,267 --> 00:08:09,433
I will help you with everything
you need.

153
00:08:11,533 --> 00:08:15,267
Remember, what you're always say
to me before?

154
00:08:15,400 --> 00:08:17,067
We can get through this.

155
00:08:17,967 --> 00:08:19,000
Okay?

156
00:08:19,133 --> 00:08:29,100
[Music continues]

157
00:08:41,233 --> 00:08:42,833
Mr. and Mrs. Torrecampo,

158
00:08:42,967 --> 00:08:45,633
Jasmine's treatment will last
about a week.

159
00:08:45,767 --> 00:08:48,433
She will need to stay
in the hospital

160
00:08:48,567 --> 00:08:51,100
while her immune system
recovers.

161
00:08:51,233 --> 00:08:56,767
We also need to monitor
possible allergic reactions

162
00:08:56,933 --> 00:08:58,667
or side effects.

163
00:09:01,000 --> 00:09:02,233
Okay, Doctor. Thank you.

164
00:09:02,367 --> 00:09:03,167
- Thank you.
- I will step out now.

165
00:09:03,300 --> 00:09:04,467
- Excuse me.
- Thank you.

166
00:09:08,300 --> 00:09:11,167
I know you are afraid
of the treatment.

167
00:09:11,300 --> 00:09:13,000
Do not worry, my child.

168
00:09:13,133 --> 00:09:15,267
Your father and I
are always here.

169
00:09:18,333 --> 00:09:19,400
I know, Mom.

170
00:09:20,600 --> 00:09:22,633
I am just glad you are here.

171
00:09:25,100 --> 00:09:29,300
I am sorry you cannot find
Grandma

172
00:09:29,467 --> 00:09:31,567
because you have to take care
of me.

173
00:09:33,333 --> 00:09:36,000
I just added to your worries.

174
00:09:36,133 --> 00:09:37,633
My child, listen to me.

175
00:09:38,667 --> 00:09:41,800
You were never a burden to me.

176
00:09:41,933 --> 00:09:43,300
You are my strength.

177
00:09:44,167 --> 00:09:47,767
No matter what happens,
you come first.

178
00:09:47,900 --> 00:09:50,667
I only wish for you
to get better.

179
00:09:50,800 --> 00:09:52,900
Be strong, Jasmine.

180
00:09:53,033 --> 00:09:55,433
I hope when I leave here,

181
00:09:55,567 --> 00:10:00,167
we find Grandma
so we can be whole again.

182
00:10:00,300 --> 00:10:02,300
So we can be happy again.

183
00:10:03,233 --> 00:10:11,500
[Dramatic]

184
00:10:11,633 --> 00:10:12,933
Stop crying, okay?

185
00:10:18,200 --> 00:10:20,000
You.

186
00:10:20,133 --> 00:10:23,600
Stay right here, okay.

187
00:10:23,733 --> 00:10:25,200
Do not leave me.

188
00:10:25,333 --> 00:10:28,700
Stay here with me.

189
00:10:28,833 --> 00:10:29,633
Stay here.

190
00:10:29,767 --> 00:10:31,067
Uncle Jobert.

191
00:10:32,700 --> 00:10:34,033
Ashley.

192
00:10:38,833 --> 00:10:43,267
Uncle Jobert,
why do you look sad?

193
00:10:44,500 --> 00:10:47,667
I am worried about Mom

194
00:10:47,800 --> 00:10:51,367
and Baby Jasmine
at the hospital.

195
00:10:54,633 --> 00:10:56,267
I am worried too.

196
00:10:56,400 --> 00:10:58,867
But let us not be sad,
Uncle Jobert.

197
00:10:59,567 --> 00:11:01,267
Jasmine is in the hospital

198
00:11:01,400 --> 00:11:04,300
so the doctors can make her
better.

199
00:11:06,200 --> 00:11:11,667
But I am still
worried about Mom.

200
00:11:14,967 --> 00:11:18,233
I am sure she will be okay,
Uncle Jobert.

201
00:11:19,933 --> 00:11:23,233
Maybe she just needs time
to think.

202
00:11:24,200 --> 00:11:25,667
To heal.

203
00:11:26,533 --> 00:11:28,333
[Dramatic]

204
00:11:28,467 --> 00:11:30,800
Oh, I know, Uncle Jobert.

205
00:11:31,800 --> 00:11:34,700
I thought of a way so we will
not be sad anymore.

206
00:11:34,833 --> 00:11:37,933
[Music continues]

207
00:11:48,233 --> 00:11:52,667
<i>I know you are your father's
favorite.</i>

208
00:11:53,100 --> 00:11:57,500
<i>And I know you are
following his path.</i>

209
00:11:57,633 --> 00:12:02,967
<i>But, please,
do not become like him.</i>

210
00:12:03,100 --> 00:12:06,333
<i> Please, Paolo, listen to me!</i>

211
00:12:09,100 --> 00:12:10,833
<i> [Sobbing]</i>

212
00:12:10,967 --> 00:12:18,400
<i>I am trying to endure it,
but I am breaking down.</i>

213
00:12:18,567 --> 00:12:21,467
<i>Do not be as evil
as your father.</i>

214
00:12:21,600 --> 00:12:24,033
<i> Please!</i>

215
00:12:34,733 --> 00:12:35,633
Love?

216
00:12:39,767 --> 00:12:43,900
Jasmine's chemotherapy infusion
is starting.

217
00:12:44,033 --> 00:12:45,067
Are you okay?

218
00:12:48,467 --> 00:12:51,333
I just need to leave.

219
00:12:52,367 --> 00:12:53,700
I will go home for a while.

220
00:12:55,767 --> 00:12:57,600
I have something important
to take care of.

221
00:12:59,633 --> 00:13:00,533
What is it?

222
00:13:01,900 --> 00:13:05,767
Something I should have done
a long time ago.

223
00:13:07,300 --> 00:13:10,133
After that,

224
00:13:10,500 --> 00:13:11,600
everything will be fine.

225
00:13:14,700 --> 00:13:15,367
I will come back.

226
00:13:17,267 --> 00:13:18,200
I promise you.

227
00:13:46,067 --> 00:13:46,733
Paolo!

228
00:13:46,867 --> 00:13:48,567
Why are you avoiding me?

229
00:13:48,967 --> 00:13:50,267
Are you feeling guilty?

230
00:13:50,400 --> 00:13:51,267
Keep your voice down!

231
00:13:51,400 --> 00:13:52,433
Someone might hear you!

232
00:13:53,700 --> 00:13:56,600
Marj only brings problems
into your life.

233
00:13:56,767 --> 00:13:58,100
All I give you is happiness.

234
00:13:58,233 --> 00:14:00,900
- Why do you choose her over me?
- Let go of me!

235
00:14:02,400 --> 00:14:03,867
Of course.

236
00:14:04,000 --> 00:14:04,767
She is my wife.

237
00:14:04,900 --> 00:14:07,000
I will be there for her.

238
00:14:07,133 --> 00:14:09,267
Marj is going through so much.

239
00:14:09,400 --> 00:14:11,100
I am the only one
she can rely on.

240
00:14:12,500 --> 00:14:14,500
So, I should be the one
to suffer?

241
00:14:14,633 --> 00:14:15,833
It's her mother's fault

242
00:14:15,967 --> 00:14:18,467
if she can't rely on someone.

243
00:14:18,600 --> 00:14:21,267
Did we not agree this
was just for fun?

244
00:14:22,800 --> 00:14:24,833
Why are you becoming demanding?

245
00:14:27,600 --> 00:14:29,633
I'm giving you, everything.

246
00:14:29,767 --> 00:14:31,433
I give you everything you want.

247
00:14:31,567 --> 00:14:34,067
Did I ever neglect you
and Ashley?

248
00:14:34,200 --> 00:14:36,933
What's wrong if I ask for more
attention?

249
00:14:37,067 --> 00:14:40,300
You also enjoy
every time we are together.

250
00:14:40,433 --> 00:14:42,633
This is not we talked before.

251
00:14:42,767 --> 00:14:44,833
I don't want this anymore!

252
00:14:44,967 --> 00:14:46,500
- What?
- This is over.

253
00:14:46,633 --> 00:14:48,167
[TENSE]

254
00:14:48,300 --> 00:14:49,267
No.

255
00:14:50,000 --> 00:14:51,000
You're not serious, Paolo.

256
00:14:51,133 --> 00:14:52,333
I am.

257
00:14:52,467 --> 00:14:57,267
Let's end this!

258
00:14:57,400 --> 00:15:01,367
Ashley is Edward's daughter!

259
00:15:01,500 --> 00:15:04,000
Did we talked about that, right?

260
00:15:04,167 --> 00:15:06,367
- But I want this, Paolo.
- That if we don't want,

261
00:15:06,500 --> 00:15:08,400
we stop!

262
00:15:08,533 --> 00:15:09,733
And I don't want.

263
00:15:09,867 --> 00:15:10,733
Paolo, I want to, please!

264
00:15:10,867 --> 00:15:12,033
No, we're done!

265
00:15:12,167 --> 00:15:14,400
What we have is great!

266
00:15:14,533 --> 00:15:17,433
Why do we have to stop it?

267
00:15:17,567 --> 00:15:20,000
Paolo, please think
before you decide.

268
00:15:20,133 --> 00:15:22,300
This before you decide.

269
00:15:22,433 --> 00:15:23,467
I did.

270
00:15:23,600 --> 00:15:25,633
I have decided.

271
00:15:25,767 --> 00:15:29,200
We are ending this, right here,
right now.

272
00:15:35,300 --> 00:15:37,733
Then you just click here.

273
00:15:37,867 --> 00:15:39,733
So, you can start recording.

274
00:15:39,867 --> 00:15:42,367
First, we are going to check
your gallery.

275
00:15:42,500 --> 00:15:45,867
If you have any videos here.

276
00:15:46,000 --> 00:15:47,033
There.

277
00:15:47,167 --> 00:15:48,700
Should I try to upload this?

278
00:15:48,833 --> 00:15:53,033
If we click that, there,
you can see the upload button.

279
00:15:53,167 --> 00:15:53,733
There!

280
00:15:53,867 --> 00:15:56,033
[LAUGHING]

281
00:15:56,167 --> 00:15:57,233
Okay, Uncle Jobert.

282
00:15:57,367 --> 00:15:59,367
I'll get some juice,

283
00:15:59,500 --> 00:16:01,433
and I'll also get one for you,
okay?

284
00:16:01,567 --> 00:16:02,533
I'll be back.

285
00:16:02,667 --> 00:16:04,367
Here's your phone.

286
00:16:04,500 --> 00:16:07,200
- Thank you, Ashley.
- I'll be back.

287
00:16:19,800 --> 00:16:21,467
Let's video, Pong.

288
00:16:23,433 --> 00:16:24,800
I'll take a video of you, Pong.

289
00:16:25,833 --> 00:16:26,500
Come on.

290
00:16:27,433 --> 00:16:28,400
Come here.

291
00:16:34,600 --> 00:16:35,567
- Let go of me!
- No!

292
00:16:35,700 --> 00:16:37,200
- I said let go of me!
- No!

293
00:16:37,333 --> 00:16:38,867
I should also have to say you
this.

294
00:16:40,067 --> 00:16:42,433
If you have decide to break up
with me,

295
00:16:43,500 --> 00:16:45,900
at least grant my last wish.

296
00:16:47,967 --> 00:16:49,167
What's that?

297
00:16:49,300 --> 00:16:50,433
Let's do it!

298
00:16:52,533 --> 00:16:56,800
Mommy, I feel like throwing up.

299
00:16:58,233 --> 00:17:00,233
That is just a side effect
of your medicine.

300
00:17:00,367 --> 00:17:01,533
Like before?

301
00:17:05,433 --> 00:17:06,633
Where is Dad?

302
00:17:08,233 --> 00:17:10,900
He went home for a while.

303
00:17:11,033 --> 00:17:13,267
But he will come back soon.

304
00:17:16,167 --> 00:17:19,467
Please tell him to hurry.

305
00:17:21,500 --> 00:17:24,100
I will feel braver
if he is here.

306
00:17:35,467 --> 00:17:36,567
<i> Where are you?</i>

307
00:17:46,733 --> 00:17:48,333
Paolo, one last time.

308
00:17:50,367 --> 00:17:52,300
One last moment together.

309
00:17:53,133 --> 00:17:56,833
An angry, sweaty, hard bang,
Paolo.

310
00:17:58,100 --> 00:18:00,400
Just a remembrance for all
the time we have spent together.

311
00:18:01,800 --> 00:18:02,900
[HUFFS]

312
00:18:06,167 --> 00:18:13,400
[INTENSE]

313
00:18:15,333 --> 00:18:15,967
[Huffs]

314
00:18:16,333 --> 00:18:17,900
That is ridiculous!

315
00:18:18,233 --> 00:18:19,933
Is it?

316
00:18:20,067 --> 00:18:21,900
You did not think it was
ridiculous

317
00:18:22,067 --> 00:18:25,333
when we were doing that
for the past few weeks.

318
00:18:25,467 --> 00:18:29,467
Besides, Paolo, we deserve
to end this properly.

319
00:18:30,500 --> 00:18:36,967
Not in a way that makes me feel
like you are throwing me away.

320
00:18:39,800 --> 00:18:40,967
Thea, that is not true.

321
00:18:41,100 --> 00:18:43,100
But, Paolo, that is how I feel.

322
00:18:44,500 --> 00:18:48,567
[Sobbing]

323
00:18:48,700 --> 00:18:50,500
Like I am nothing.

324
00:18:53,200 --> 00:18:56,200
Like you only use me
when you are stressed.

325
00:18:56,367 --> 00:19:02,433
Especially when work makes you
feel badly about yourself.

326
00:19:05,900 --> 00:19:07,467
You know that is not true.

327
00:19:10,400 --> 00:19:11,933
Then please give me this.

328
00:19:13,200 --> 00:19:16,833
Grant me my final request.

329
00:19:16,967 --> 00:19:18,733
[Brief contact]

330
00:19:18,867 --> 00:19:22,867
Before I finally walk away
from you and your life.

331
00:19:23,000 --> 00:19:25,533
[Intense]

332
00:19:25,667 --> 00:19:27,200
I will never interfere
in your marriage.

333
00:19:27,333 --> 00:19:28,400
I promise you.

334
00:19:30,633 --> 00:19:31,733
Paolo, please.

335
00:19:31,867 --> 00:19:33,233
[Heavy breathing]

336
00:19:33,367 --> 00:19:35,767
[Intense]

337
00:19:54,833 --> 00:20:03,567
[Machine beeping]

338
00:20:03,733 --> 00:20:04,933
[Phone keys clicking]

339
00:20:05,067 --> 00:20:06,800
[Line ringing]

340
00:20:06,933 --> 00:20:08,500
[Music continues]

341
00:20:29,333 --> 00:20:31,267
Here, here, Pong.

342
00:20:31,600 --> 00:20:32,500
There.

343
00:20:32,633 --> 00:20:34,500
[Chuckles]

344
00:20:34,633 --> 00:20:39,400
Let us send this
to Baby Jasmine.

345
00:20:39,567 --> 00:20:44,533
Jobert will send this
so she will be happy.

346
00:20:44,667 --> 00:20:45,700
[Chuckles]

347
00:20:49,367 --> 00:20:51,967
[Intense]

348
00:20:52,100 --> 00:20:53,167
Uncle Jobert?

349
00:20:55,033 --> 00:20:56,767
Where did he go?

350
00:20:56,900 --> 00:20:58,033
Uncle Jobert?

351
00:21:02,700 --> 00:21:04,033
Uncle Jobert!

352
00:21:04,167 --> 00:21:09,000
[Music continues]

353
00:21:09,167 --> 00:21:10,933
There, Pong.

354
00:21:12,667 --> 00:21:18,733
[Intense]

355
00:21:33,500 --> 00:21:34,467
[Strained breathing]

356
00:21:34,600 --> 00:21:43,467
[Music continues]

357
00:21:43,633 --> 00:21:44,900
[Intense]

358
00:21:45,033 --> 00:21:46,733
[Heavy breathing]

359
00:21:46,867 --> 00:21:48,533
[Music continues]

360
00:21:48,667 --> 00:21:53,367
[Intense]

361
00:21:53,500 --> 00:21:55,433
[Music continues]

362
00:21:56,567 --> 00:22:00,333
[Intense]

363
00:22:07,833 --> 00:22:09,300
Kind Brother!

364
00:22:12,733 --> 00:22:13,600
Jobert.

365
00:22:15,467 --> 00:22:16,633
Jobert!

366
00:22:16,767 --> 00:22:17,433
Jobert!

367
00:22:17,567 --> 00:22:23,100
[Intense]

368
00:22:23,233 --> 00:22:24,733
[Exclaiming]

369
00:22:24,867 --> 00:22:26,633
[Intense]

370
00:22:26,767 --> 00:22:29,100
[Music continues]

371
00:22:29,233 --> 00:22:36,033
[Intense]

372
00:22:42,700 --> 00:22:43,767
This is exactly
what I was talking about.

373
00:22:43,900 --> 00:22:45,000
That is why I wanted to stop!

374
00:22:45,133 --> 00:22:47,333
Before we blame each other,
let us go to Jobert.

375
00:22:47,467 --> 00:22:48,800
It looks like he recorded us!

376
00:22:52,233 --> 00:22:53,033
Come on!

377
00:22:53,167 --> 00:22:56,767
[Intense]

378
00:22:56,900 --> 00:22:58,933
Jobert!

379
00:22:59,067 --> 00:22:59,933
Jobert!

380
00:23:04,800 --> 00:23:05,633
[Intense]

381
00:23:06,033 --> 00:23:06,867
Jobert!

382
00:23:07,433 --> 00:23:08,533
Jobert!

383
00:23:08,667 --> 00:23:09,967
[Intense]

384
00:23:11,800 --> 00:23:12,433
I am over here.

385
00:23:12,567 --> 00:23:13,633
[Speaks indistinctly]

386
00:23:13,767 --> 00:23:15,367
Jobert!

387
00:23:15,500 --> 00:23:17,600
[Intense]

388
00:23:17,733 --> 00:23:20,900
[Music continues]

389
00:23:34,667 --> 00:23:35,267
Jobert!

390
00:23:35,400 --> 00:23:36,533
Give me your phone!

391
00:23:38,333 --> 00:23:40,833
Do not make me angry!

392
00:23:40,967 --> 00:23:42,667
- Give me your phone now!
- No! No!

393
00:23:42,800 --> 00:23:43,567
- Where is it?
- No!

394
00:23:43,700 --> 00:23:44,700
Don't be stubborn!

395
00:23:44,833 --> 00:23:45,933
Sister!

396
00:23:46,067 --> 00:23:53,967
[Intense]

397
00:23:54,100 --> 00:23:56,667
[Exclaiming]

398
00:23:56,833 --> 00:23:59,367
I will tell this to my sister!

399
00:23:59,500 --> 00:24:07,033
[Music continues]

400
00:24:07,167 --> 00:24:08,433
Jobert!

401
00:24:08,567 --> 00:24:13,667
[Suspenseful]

402
00:24:21,100 --> 00:24:31,067
[Music continues]

403
00:24:35,100 --> 00:24:36,833
Jobert!

404
00:24:36,967 --> 00:24:38,267
Mom, have you seen...

405
00:24:39,867 --> 00:24:41,133
Uncle Jobert!

406
00:24:44,467 --> 00:24:46,867
[Panting]

407
00:24:47,000 --> 00:24:48,067
Oh my God!

408
00:24:51,467 --> 00:24:52,800
What happened, Thea?

409
00:24:52,933 --> 00:24:53,900
I do not know.

410
00:24:54,033 --> 00:24:55,533
I just found him like this!

411
00:24:55,667 --> 00:24:59,233
He may not have seen the stairs
or he may have slipped!

412
00:24:59,367 --> 00:25:02,600
[Yolly speaks indistinctly]

413
00:25:02,767 --> 00:25:04,633
[Intense]

414
00:25:04,867 --> 00:25:05,700
He still has a pulse.

415
00:25:05,833 --> 00:25:07,533
Yolly, call an ambulance!

416
00:25:07,667 --> 00:25:13,933
[Intense]

417
00:25:21,400 --> 00:25:22,900
Let us lift him.
Take him to the hospital.

418
00:25:25,233 --> 00:25:26,667
One, two, three!

419
00:25:26,800 --> 00:25:28,000
Slowly, Oscar!

420
00:25:28,133 --> 00:25:36,867
[Intense]

421
00:25:37,033 --> 00:25:38,533
Do not stop looking for it.

422
00:25:38,667 --> 00:25:39,833
I will look in the garden too.

423
00:25:39,967 --> 00:25:40,967
This is a phone, right?

424
00:25:41,100 --> 00:25:41,933
Why is this here?

425
00:25:42,067 --> 00:25:43,633
This is Uncle Jobert's phone!

426
00:25:43,767 --> 00:25:44,800
Ashley gave it.

427
00:25:44,933 --> 00:25:45,867
You may want to have it.

428
00:25:46,000 --> 00:25:47,367
Fix this, Paolo.

429
00:25:47,667 --> 00:25:49,667
Make sure this
does not get worse.

430
00:25:49,800 --> 00:25:52,733
Otherwise, our family
will be destroyed.

431
00:25:52,867 --> 00:25:54,633
My goodness!

432
00:25:54,767 --> 00:25:55,900
You are shameless!

433
00:25:56,033 --> 00:25:57,100
You have been exposed!

434
00:25:57,233 --> 00:25:59,200
Did you ever truly love me?

435
00:25:59,333 --> 00:26:03,500
If you loved me,
you would not hurt me!

436
00:26:03,633 --> 00:26:06,267
You even went after
your sibling's spouse!

437
00:26:06,400 --> 00:26:07,233
What kind of sibling are you?

438
00:26:07,367 --> 00:26:09,200
You even slept with my spouse?

439
00:26:09,367 --> 00:26:11,067
[Intense]

440
00:26:11,367 --> 00:26:12,333
Enough with the lies.

441
00:26:12,467 --> 00:26:14,567
I want to know everything!

442
00:26:14,700 --> 00:26:16,333
Everything!

443
00:26:16,667 --> 00:26:21,467
[Thump]
